title.narrative: 'Strengthened prevention and protection services to address child marriage and FGM/C

description.narrative: Following the launch of the National Costed Roadmap to end Child Marriage and FGM/C in August 2019, the Ministry of Women, Children and Youth (MoWCY), with support from UNICEF and UN Women, translated the roadmap into local languages, convened dialogues with regional bureaus, and initiated a partnership with national and local media to popularize action on the roadmap. It developed a briefing note including expected budget allocation, evidence-based strategies and interventions to be implemented which is being used in discussions officials are having with other sectors including health, education, justice and social protection. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020

title.narrative: Number of girls and women who receive prevention and protection services on FGM/C through UNICEF-supported programmes

actual.value: 2020:The programme reached 102,480 girls and women (3,128 in Oromia, 28,127 in Afar, 65,763 in Somali and 5,462 in SNNP).

title.narrative: Number of men, women,. boys and girls who participate in social mobilization platforms promoting the elimination of FGMC

actual.value: 2020:The programme reached 749,264 people (703,000 through media engagement at national level and 46,264 through other mobilization interventions).

title.narrative: Country implementing a costed national action plan or strategy to end child marriage.

actual.value: 2020:The rollout of the Roadmap continued, reflecting its interventions in plans developed by MoWCY and FAG with financial and technical support from UN agencies including UNFPA, UNICEF and CSOs. Translation into local languages and familiarization at regional and woreda levels are underway.
